rComments: She organized the tribunals placements. We had one meeting session to arrange some logistics and then we essentially never heard from her again. She sent maybe one more email out that term and seemed to be M.I.A. as she was only working part-time from my understanding. Very friendly but didn't seem very engaged.

Prof Chapman is a great prof and I am actually suprised by these comments.  She is so helpful and really loves her students and teaching.  So approachable and really wants her students to understand and engage with material.  Such a smart woman!

Chapman and Lyle are a great duo. They are both passionate about their field and I enjoyed their class. Pamela talks fast sometimes but I remedied that by listening to most of the recorded lectures they provided. Lyle should so standup.

She's the worst professor I've had to date. And, her bizarre co-teaching with Lyle is insane. How did this woman get hired? She's mean and unhelpful to students and acts as though it is our privilege to be in her class!
